snippet: The State Supreme Court on Friday set an execution date for a killer over the objection of two justices who question establishing dates when Ohio does not have any lethal drugs.
abstract: Ohio State Supreme Court sets date for execution of James Frazier over objection of two justices, who raise concern about setting date even though state does not have lethal drugs to carry out sentence.
lead_paragraph: The State Supreme Court on Friday set an execution date for a killer over the objection of two justices who question establishing dates when Ohio does not have any lethal drugs.

headline.main: Ohio: No Drugs Found as Execution List Grows
headline.print_headline: Ohio: No Drugs Found as Execution List Grows
